column5: that theory has a major hole in it
I have tried saying hi to the pickerel but it doesn't help me catch them

Kind of like an Atlantic except that it has a pointier snout, tougher scales, spiny rayed fins, different body colour, good sized,sharp, conical teeth, different habitat, is mainly a low light hunter, more prolific,....they both live underwater though so I guess they're close lookalikes.

That's all fine and dandy, but pickeral aren't being discussed.  Re-read the post title, we're talking pickreal here.  Pickreal are a little known subspecies of Walleye native only to a few very isolated pockets of ON.  Generally angled for by illiterate hayseeds.
